post_text:
There will be no school on Monday, September 14, 2020 for middle and high school students. Health and safety of students and staff remain our number one priority and for this reason we will move to a hybrid model for middle and high school students on Tuesday September 15th.

In spite of our mitigation efforts the numbers of students identified by Boone County Health have spiked these past couple of days and we currently have 50 students quarantined due to close contact. We believe if we move to a hybrid model we will be able to spread students out and turn this around quickly. On Monday, September 14th by 3:30pm, you will receive a notification of whether your student will be on an “A-Day” or “B-Day” roster. Tuesday will be an “A-Day” and we will alternate every other day of on-site school. Students who are not on-site on a given day will be required to attend in a virtual setting. Teachers will email the specifics of their class expectations to students on Monday.

Elementary students should report to school on Monday, September 14th, as usual.

post_text:
Dear Families:

We are aware of the Governor’s announcement today that schools will remain closed for the remainder of the school year. This news does not change the plans teachers have in place for the next two weeks. Expect an update next week from your teachers and principal about next steps. We will address all topics mentioned today by the governor, including future learning options, technology for all students, cleaning out lockers/desks, and how we support our Ogden return to learning plan. Our team is working quickly so that we can communicate the next steps for Ogden CSD students. Thank you for your continued partnership with our school district.

Please stay away from the high school during this drill.

shared_text:
Boone County High School Manufacturing
December 20, 2017 at 4:21 PM ·

Monsanto reps Mitch Brown and Scott Chitty (left to right) brought over 6 welding helmets and 6 pairs of welding gloves and presented them to Rick Hamilton, coordinator of Boone County High School Manufacturing program.

Monsanto is a Founding partner and they really assist us in making our facilities OSHA compliant....

They have provided lock out - tag out supplies and drop cord reels, air hose reels, safety glasses, ear protection, etc.

We really appreciate what they do for us!
